From Kenneth Gilbert Subject Re cats and pregnancy In article Klaus Hofmann writes Hello I heard that a certain disease toxoplasmosys is transmitted by cats which can harm the unborn Does anybody know about it Is it a problem to have a cat in the same apartment Having the cat around is not a problem but the pregnant woman should not change the litter Toxoplasmosis can be transmitted from the stool of some Kenneth Gilbert University of Pittsburgh General Internal Medicine not a programmer